
[1]foraging

   FOR'AGING, ppr. or a. Collecting provisions for horses and cattle, or
   wandering in search of food; ravaging; stripping. The general sent out
   a foraging party, with a guard.

   FOR'AGING, n. An inroad or incursion for forage or plunder.
